{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"d08e9d8625e05d07","type":"text","text":"\"At this point, all food tastes so vile that it makes me gag.\" Sara couldn't help complaining. Even if it was normal, it felt so extreme. \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-06-28%20PM.png)\n\nSara listed off things on her fingers, \"I've tried grilled cheese, salad, pancakes, sandwiches; even freaking coffee tastes just putrid.\" Sara sighed, \"Everything I've managed to choke down recently, well... it doesn't stay down. And I've tried a lot different foods.\" \n\n\"Oh, oh my. Things should taste different, but not vile.\" Lilith's eye got wider and she leaned forward in her chair. ","x":-948,"y":2627,"width":780,"height":720},
		{"id":"ec284b30a27e68d2","type":"text","text":"\"What do you mean by senses?\" But even as the words left her mouth, she had a feeling that she knew. \"Or... You mean like how I can feel you're both vampires, don't you?\" Sara bit her lip. \n\n\"And like how you knew to come to me to answers.\" Lilith's smile was knowing. \n\nSara wanted to argue it was because she got that flashes of memory back, but she knew that wasn't all there was to it, she could sense that too. \n\n\"It's a mixture of being able to sense and feel about the physical things around you, and instinctually feeling and knowing things that are less physical.\" Lilith held out her hand as if she were holding a ball, even though it were empty. ","x":-948,"y":3940,"width":780,"height":320},
		{"id":"74f28f0fbf5b3186","type":"text","text":"\"It's not supposed to be this bad?\" Sara felt conflicted again; if this wasn't normal, then was she ok? \n\n\"Most vampires can still eat solid human food. It doesn't taste as wonderful as before the change, or provide any real nutrition, but the flavor is... ok.\" Lilith shrugged, \"But eating doesn't cause... problems. It helps us keep up appearances, blend in among mortals.\"\n\nSara simply waited for Lilith to continue; *most* implied *not all*.\n\n\"But I have heard tales, well rumors, similar to what you are describing. Some say that of the very oldest ancient vampires have a strong aversion to solid food. The rumors say that, over the centuries, they have developed such an affinity for the dark power of the vampires, that their stomachs have withered. Which causes them to permanently lose their ability to keep down anything solid, according to these rumors.\" Lilith held out a hand, \"If you would like, I can try to use my senses to see if I can tell what's going on?\"","x":-948,"y":3460,"width":780,"height":420},
		{"id":"ce6914bd65538672","type":"text","text":"Sara swallowed. She had used this new vampire ability without even trying; without even knowing she had them. She nodded, \"Yes, if you can tell what's going on, or can I sense myself?\" she wondered aloud. She couldn't at the moment, but maybe she simply didn't know how.  \n\nLilith shook her head. \"You can't sense your own body. The conscious mind gets in the way. Vampiric sensing relies of being in tune with the darkness. But feeling you own body, there's the reflex to use your nerve endings, which simply confuses things. Besides, ignoring your own nervous system would come at a cost, you don't want to lose your mind-body connection.\" \n\n<!-- I like this, because in time, Sara can learn to override the conscious mind part, to actually feel the darkness instead of her nerves when she wants to. Though it will be tricky and come with meaning she needs (at least?) a moment to listen to her nerves again. It's not necessarily good for her to disconnect from her nervous system, but maybe it's necessary alone in Strangerville? Once Don is infected she is functionally alone. -->","x":-948,"y":4320,"width":780,"height":400},
		{"id":"83d5d21103e88f7b","type":"text","text":"Sara swallowed, and looked down at her midsection. So her gut was trashed? For good? But she was still pregnant, her belly was clearly growing, and she needed to feed both of them... to feed. She was a *vampire* that needed to *feed*. \"So, are you saying I need to drink blood then?\" At first thought made her skin crawl. But as she pictured doing so, a thirsty hunger awoke within her. One that made the idea sound so wonderful... that part of her body shivered. Sara wasn't sure rather it was from disgust, fear, or... desire. \n\n\"The rumors say that fresh blood is the only thing those vampires can only consume, but I don't know if that's true. It is rumors.\" ","x":-1148,"y":5840,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"bb9f7e7e97bc49fd","type":"text","text":"\"Maybe... I guess?\" Sara's reply was uneasy. She didn't actually know when each had started, but somehow she felt 'yes' was the right answer. \n\n\"That is...\" Lilith paused, \"unusual. I'm not aware of anyone who turned while with child. I don't know if the two could have interacted in some way? And together caused your insides to wither.\"","x":-1240,"y":6360,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1a90bf367c92d3ce","type":"text","text":"Lilith got quiet and seemed to be deep in concentrating. Part of Sara thought it was odd having someone she barely knew close like this, but part of her was just fine with it. Lilith didn't feel as much like a stranger as she should have. \n\n\"Yes...\" Lilith paused. \"your stomach has withered, and is in bad shape. It needs... a break for anything solid. No surprise there... As far as why, let's see here. Ah, right there. I see, it was a combination. The transformation and the pregnancy, I suppose you could say it's like an interaction.\" Lilith closed her eyes, lowered her hands, and took a deep breath. \"Sorry, that's all I can do for now.\"\n\n\"I'm not sure I get what you mean by interaction. Has it hurt the baby?\"\n\n\"No, she is fine. A bit thirsty, but new vampires sometimes are. ","x":-948,"y":5400,"width":780,"height":340},
		{"id":"ba8931403c5441ab","type":"text","text":"Not sure what to say, Sara went back to the beginning. \"I guess it started with things tasting different.\" \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-04-23%20PM.png)\n\n\"Well of course. What humans eat won't have the same flavor. We aren't human.\" Lilith's tone was soft. \"Even during transformation, such changes are normal.\" ","x":-948,"y":1970,"width":780,"height":620},
		{"id":"0936e62aaa285664","type":"text","text":"\"Are you ok?\" Lilith seemed genuine, and trustworthy... somehow. \n\nNot sure what to say, Sara went back to the beginning. \"I guess it started with things tasting different.\" \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-04-23%20PM.png)\n\n\"Well of course. What humans eat won't have the same flavor. We aren't human.\" Lilith's tone was soft and caring. \"Even during transformation, such changes are normal.\"","x":-2720,"y":1970,"width":780,"height":620},
		{"id":"1c1a75d5dc51b72e","type":"text","text":"Lilith kinda ignores her being sick? Lilith would be able to hear it, and I mean Sara said that what was happening. \n\nMaybe it works better without Lilith asking if she's ok, not because she doesn't care, but because Lilith is a bit confused, and Sara seems distressed, and well this is a lot to take in. Maybe Lilith can sense that Sara needs a moment. ","x":-1800,"y":1540,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1284b5375c758530","type":"text","text":"So here's Lilith is kinda thinking like \"so that's where she wants to start?\" Maybe Lilith can feel that Sara doesn't want to talk about pukling her guts out. ","x":-1600,"y":2227,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"ad9a70b807504031","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/Chapters/2.04-TalkToVampires.md","x":-948,"y":-4460,"width":780,"height":4860},
		{"id":"d977b64818765b81","type":"text","text":"Sara rushed to follow where Lilith had went,\n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_11-07-00%20AM.png)\n\nand barely made it in time before she was sick several times. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_1-52-19%20PM.png)\n\nWhen the vomiting stopped long enough for Sara to get down on her knees, she held her belly with her left hand while she gripped the seat with her right to help keep herself up. More had already come up than she had expected, but she knew the feeling in her gut: it wasn't done. She just tried to breath at least a few putrid breathes before her stomach started up again.  \n\n----\n\nAfter a few more times of puking and pauses where she tried to breath, the nauseous feeling finally passed. Sara was shaky on her feet. She grabbed the edge of the sink to help pull herself up. She used it to rinse her mouth out. Sara held the edge of the sink as she tried to breath slowly. \n\nShe felt weak as she stumbled back to the living room, and sat on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. It was all so much to take in. ","x":-948,"y":540,"width":780,"height":1340},
		{"id":"27a5795745c01890","type":"text","text":"Maybe Sara **needs** to sit, like her body is wiped after what it just went through, but she doesn't want to face these near strangers. But maybe she can tell Lilith isn't in the parlor anymore?\n\nOr maybe she comes out there, and Lilith can tell she needs a minute, so Lilith makes up some excuse to leave?\n\nSara sat across from Lilith, her fellow vampire. It was all too much to take in. \n\nLilith take a breath as she focused her dark magic, \"I know this is quite improper, but would it bother you if I \"","x":-140,"y":1940,"width":780,"height":400},
		{"id":"a9b6d19727ae9849","type":"text","text":"Sara rushed after Lilith,\n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_11-07-00%20AM.png)\n\nand barely made it in time before she was sick several times. \n\nDuring one of the pauses, she managed to herself get lowered to her knees. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_1-14-55%20PM.png)\n\nSara held her belly with her left hand while she gripped the seat with her right to help keep herself up. More had already come up than she had expected, but she knew the feeling in her gut: it wasn't done. \n\n----\n\nAfter a few more times of puking and pauses where she tried to breath, the nauseous feeling finally passed. Sara was shaky on her feet. She grabbed the edge of the sink to help pull herself up. She used it to rinse her mouth out. Sara held the edge of the sink as she tried to breath slowly. \n\nShe felt weak as she stumbled back to the living room, and sat on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. It was all so much to take in. ","x":1280,"y":320,"width":780,"height":1340},
		{"id":"0e1e0193dd6df84c","type":"text","text":"\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-01-00%20PM.png)\n\nSara rushed after her and barely made it in time,\n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-01-22%20PM.png)\n\nfor everything she had eaten for dinner to force it's way back out of her. As it did, her racing thoughts slowed back down. She didn't know **how** she knew it was all true, but she could feel it in her bones: not only were vampires real, she now was one. \n\nSara moved to the sink, rinsed her mouth, and gripped the sink as she tried to breath slowly. She felt weak as she stumbled back to the living room, and sat on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. It was all so much to take in. ","x":2160,"y":380,"width":780,"height":1160},
		{"id":"1d06ff80ccddb2ad","type":"text","text":"If Lilith can sense Sara, is the bond between a maker and a vampire akin to like a mother? Or is it very different in nature? \n\nI don't know part of me is thinking about having Lilith waiting outside bathroom door, to help Sarah back to the couch\n\nAnd part of me thinking about maybe Sarah can get to the couch by herself. She's a little shaky for a moment, but as the pain passes, her vampire body is still able to move and such. And maybe having Sarah sitting there on the couch, and thinking it was weird. It was also overwhelming and she had the feeling like she just wanted to be alone, but somehow Lilith being there didn't bother her. As if she already was alone? It did make sense. ","x":-140,"y":1520,"width":780,"height":400},
		{"id":"68dd03bf011bcae0","type":"text","text":"So I'm looking at this and I'm thinking about the stuff below. \n\nSara might not need space after she's sick, because she might not actually be upset about throwing up. That might not really bother her so much because of reasons in other cards. \n\nI mean sure she's reeling from the whole I'm a vampire now thing, ","x":1140,"y":1920,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"211ec92f767bed8b","type":"text","text":"\"But I have heard tales, rumors. Some say that a few of the very oldest vampires have stomachs that have withered. They say that these vampires are so deeply in touch with the dark power that, after centuries, they permanently lost their ability to keep down anything solid.\" Lilith paused, \"You have such a strong natural affinity for the dark power... have you been pregnant through at least most of your transformation?\"","x":-2140,"y":3433,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"e97cb66e1fc90ee7","type":"text","text":"\"What you're describing, it reminds me of some rumors I've heard. Some claim that a few of the very oldest vampires have an aversion to eating solid food. That, over the centuries, they gained such an affinity for the dark power of the vampires that their stomach shived up and withered. Leaving them dependent on blood.\" ","x":-1740,"y":3433,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"f2ab7aa8ae26ba0c","type":"text","text":"Maybe some vampires get their \"vampire taste buds\" while they're transforming and some get them when the transformation is over. \n\nSara got something else entirely. And maybe once she's transformed, food tastes even worse (not that she's inclined to taste it ever again). I mean there is that omelet she makes for Jane, and maybe she tried licking something to make sure it tasted fine, and had to go rinse her tongue? Though making an omelet doesn't require tasting it? Maybe her sense of smell is off? Or maybe it's just been while so she's rusty and isn't sure if she remembered all the steps because Jane has been handling the cooking? ","x":2760,"y":2551,"width":400,"height":528},
		{"id":"bf59a27a96bb6e8b","type":"text","text":"Her stomach has finished withering because her transformation is over. Her stomach not in the in between type of state, where it's still changing from the transformation (which even in normal situations is very painful).\n\nI'm thinking that during the transformation, her body was basically confused as this slow \"crash\" happened. \n\nThe vampire transformation is supposed to convert the digestive track to be able to use blood to keep the body alive. But because of the pregnancy, the transformation didn't happen in the normal fashion. Between the hormones and the altered needs/demands on her body and the dark magic, her biological \"wires\" got crossed. Like two medications having an interaction, even when the person can take both separately. I mean sure her affinity for the dark power played a role, a nature/nurture mix (or \"prefect storm\"). \n\nBut once her transformation is complete, her stomach has firmly \"made up it's mind\" on what her body needs. It's not half in half out, or half wanting blood and half wanting food (while only taking in food and not being fully able to digest it). It wants blood and it's rejecting everything solid. Decision made. \n\nHer body isn't trying to digest the food anymore. Before it sort of could, so it sort of was. But only sort of, it also sort of wasn't, and that's why she was throwing up so often. It had to do something with the parts it couldn't deal with, so it vomited them back up. While also trying to digest the parts it could. \n\nBut now, none of that trying to digest & reject at the same time stuff. Her gut says it's all got to go. While the removal process isn't comfortable, it does get her body to a point where her gut is ok with things again. Before it was trying to do both and once so it never reached a sort of \"all done, happy with things now\" point, because there wasn't one in this sort of stalemate tug of war. But the transformation finished and the chaos is gone. \n\nSo while for a minute her gut is really upset about the food in her, once it's gone, things finally settle for the first time since before this all started.","x":2000,"y":2678,"width":660,"height":875},
		{"id":"32793ded4ce8f81d","type":"text","text":"This is clearing her withered stomach (and/or entire withered gut) so it can take in blood. So once it's empty, she probably feels a lot better before too long. And this means her thirst can come online. Where as before, all this stuff it couldn't even pass let alone digest was in the way. \n\nSo of course she starts to feel better. Her body has gotten rid of the stuff that isn't food to her. ","x":2000,"y":2393,"width":660,"height":244},
		{"id":"79183229a38ea651","type":"text","text":"Given her new vampire state (fully transformed), while throwing up might feel worse as it's happening, but honestly she would probably feel much better pretty soon after it's over. \n\nFor one thing, now that she is actually a vampire, her hunger is gone. Like gone gone. \n\nThe food leaving her body might even feel different. As a human, food is supposed to stay down. As a vampire, isn't not something her body needs. ","x":1400,"y":2515,"width":400,"height":600},
		{"id":"d37a0e4788757bdf","type":"text","text":"Yes not being able to workout gets to her, but she uses exercise to regulate her emotions, especially her anger. \n\nShe is a hot head, but because she works out, she's not an angry person. Take away the exercise, and she at least has a much harder time not being angry. ","x":320,"y":2715,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"ee6d9b3aa574258f","type":"text","text":"Sara is a professional athlete. Pain and discomfort are part of her world. I mean yes she tries to avoid injuries, but I'm not sure pro's actually can avoid at least some discomfort? Insert the movie Stick It where she talks about peeling callouses the size of quarters off your fingers or is a lot of pain from being sore form taking a break in her training. At the very least, the being sore part I know is true. Heck I started taking short walks and one of my heels wasn't happy about it for a day or two. So even if she doesn't get like a broken leg or anything serious like that, surely at least minor discomfort is just part of the package? And probably more the minor. She's someone who is in touch with her body, she would have to be, and she used to it not feeling well sometimes. Plus she probably know staying calm helps? So maybe she's not that emotional upset over who she physically feels. Though she is needing a moment to process being a vampire","x":860,"y":2515,"width":460,"height":601},
		{"id":"e20f3f4d4d84a7a3","type":"text","text":"Though, to be clear, this is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that war doesn't have winners, just survivors. That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic has been fundamentally rebuilding her body into the powering magical being she is becoming. But this isn't resolved by the vampire side winning. The vampire side does not trash the gut. Normal vampires can eat regular human food if they want to, no issues at all (they don't even have to choke it down, they can just eat it, and it tastes fine; nothing really tastes amazing to them, but it certainly doesn't taste like cardboard, things just taste okay instead of delicious). This is like a drug interaction that has left behind permanent organ damage even after the drugs have cleared the system. \n\nOh and even the pregnancy hasn't been a stable thing. Sara's unborn child, Anne is transformed too. Sara doesn't know it when she knocks on Lilith's door, but she is a vampire pregnant with a vampire. \n\nSo not only was there what normal pregnancy does to a human body, and not only was there what a typical vampire transformation involves going on, and not only where the two interacting badly, on top of all of that, the fetus was undue going a vampire transformation process. It all contributed to Sara's transformation ending with her stomach withering. As far as why she didn't puke her guts out when the black smoke took her, idk, it needing just a bit of time checks out for me? Like sure her body is done changing, but it still need to figure out how to operate itself. And the emotional turmoil helps it along there. ","x":2000,"y":3680,"width":660,"height":680},
		{"id":"33d6a28e237adfdd","type":"text","text":"Should Sara have bandages sometimes? Or if I can find a knee brace mod, maybe she sometimes wears one when she pulls something? \n\nTo help visually show this? \n\nOh maybe there's ice pack or ice bath mods???","x":740,"y":3360,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"b430b5bdaada4b0c","type":"text","text":"- [ ] Does Sara remember biting Lilith's wrist and drinking vampire blood? ","x":70,"y":-295,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1c597003476b819a","type":"text","text":"The notes about Sara's gut calming down is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that \"war doesn't have winners, just survivors.\" - That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic has been fundamentally rebuilding her body into the powering magical being she is becoming. But this isn't resolved by the vampire side winning. The vampire side does not trash her gut, both things going at once did. Normal vampires can eat regular human food if they want to, no issues at all (they don't even have to choke it down, they can just eat it, and it tastes fine; nothing really tastes amazing to them, but it certainly doesn't taste like cardboard, things just taste okay instead of delicious). This is like a drug interaction that has left behind permanent organ damage even after the drugs have cleared the system. \n\nOh and even the pregnancy hasn't been a stable thing either. Sara's unborn child, Anne is transformed by this too. Sara doesn't know it when she knocks on Lilith's door, but she is a vampire pregnant with a vampire at that point.  \n\nSo not only was there what normal pregnancy does to a human body, and not only was there what a typical vampire transformation involves going on, and not only where the two interacting badly, on top of all of that, the fetus was undergoing a vampire transformation process. It all contributed to Sara's transformation ending with her stomach withering. As far as why she didn't puke her guts out when the black smoke took her & the transformation completed, idk. It needing just a bit of time just this once checks out for me? Like sure her body is done changing, but it still needs to figure out how to operate itself. And maybe the emotional turmoil helps it along there a little sooner? \n\nSo like I said the main thing I want to clarify is that this is not the vampire side winning the war, this is her stomach being a destroyed battlefield after a war. If the vampire side had won she might have lost the pregnancy, but her stomach definitely would not have withered. Nothing won. That's where the drug interaction metaphor comes in, these are two things that should not be done at the same time because there are permanent consequences that would not happen if they were done at different times. But not all the consequences are bad, Anne is born a day walker. She's a full vampire, but she lacks weaknesses. Please focus on when Sara and Lilith are talking because Sara has sought out Lilith and Sara has just finished her transformation and is a vampire. There’s a few different version of this chapter (2.4), including one that’s a txt that’s a renamed obsidian canvas file, so it’s especially mess (don’t worry about the card ID numbers, obsidian doesn’t show them so you don’t need to mention them or even say you’re not going to mention them), but the content is plain text.  I’ve added some new notes looking at what sort of mental state Sara, as a pro athlete, would be in and how she would respond to this. There’s also some revision notes at the start of 2.5 that are related to this plot/arc. What parts do you like best? How do you think Sara is going to respond to this? Do the notes about body discomfort not getting to her that much make sense? \n\nThere's something else I want to clarify: The notes about Sara gut calming down is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that war doesn't have winners, just survivors. That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic","x":2780,"y":3480,"width":580,"height":760},
		{"id":"2134156319b34a13","type":"text","text":"Maybe the pain is gone, maybe is really different now? But she still thinks she needs to keep down the food. \n\nShe doesn't, she can't. She's wrong about what her body needs, but I guess I'm thinking that her thoughts have some input over this, or rather her effort to calm herself is at least delaying the gut purge? She using things like breathing to manage physical activation at this point. \n\nBut later when her mind is spinning, not only is she not calming herself, some part of her knows she doesn't need the food. Idk if her thirst is playing a role in this, and it's taking a bit to come online and push the food out of the way? I mean when babies are born for example they need a lot more to drink relative to their size because their kidneys are still learning how to properly retain fluid. I guess I'm kind of comparing this to like that, where this is all new for her body. Like yeah it's finished, but that doesn't mean it's going to hit the ground running the instant the transformation is over. I don't know I guess to me it makes a lot of sense that to some degree her body needs like at least a few minutes to figure out how to operate itself now. Because it's just been through a massive radical species change. Not death and undeath, but things are different now. And they're not even different in the way they're supposed to be, they're their own kind of different because she's not like other vampires, that would be too easy. Like yes the transformation was the process of her body going through physical change, and now her body has changed and now her body is adjusting to being changed.","x":-83,"y":-2604,"width":543,"height":664},
		{"id":"d36dd91bf9687e92","x":-1380,"y":1680,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Lilith had to admit, that was concerning. Vomiting wasn't normal for vampires, but she could also feel that her new fledgling needed some space or needed a moment. I don't know I guess I'm not sure how to phrase that, and I mean maybe it's not purely a dark sense thing, because it doesn't fully read emotions, it can tell certain things but it's not mind reading. But at the same time maybe Lilith can tell from Sara's body language? "},
		{"id":"4c24fd315b18a035","x":-80,"y":540,"width":455,"height":531,"type":"text","text":"Maybe Sara isn't truly \"alone\" on Lilith's bathroom floor. Maybe at some point Don &/or her coach's words come to her. Something like the stick coach where he's like \"you know this pain, you know you have to get through it.\"\n\nAnd maybe she doesn't understand why that's where her head goes until she stands up and is shaky. But her body is shifting to that \"oh good the garbage is gone\" type of state, but maybe that's not how her mind interprets it. Maybe to her it's familiar because it reminds her of after a hard workout. I mean it's obviously not exactly the same, but she's shaky and tired but she feels better now. \n\nAs Sara stood there, gripping the sink and trying to breathe, it was like as if something had finally clicked into place."},
		{"id":"4ab3b9cf0c4b5d51","x":420,"y":445,"width":520,"height":720,"type":"text","text":"And maybe Sara and Jane weren't just ignoring this whole thing the whole time, maybe Jane like looked it up online or on her phone or something and was like yeah there is an extreme form of morning sickness, and Sara's like \"of course there is. There's an extreme version of everything that can happen to the body.\"\n\nI mean I'll need to look up how that works and what things kind of help it, but basically maybe they were treating it like it was just that like super extreme ridiculous version of morning sickness, and that's why they weren't like crazy worried about it? I mean it's concerning it's absolutely concerning, but it's not like why weren't they in the emergency room?\n\nAnd I mean maybe Sarah did see whatever sort of like medical person they have for her team or whatever sports she play, I mean surely there's some sort of medical professional around somewhere that's like not that out of the ordinary for her to see. Again professional athlete, to some degree this is an investment. Because her body is her asset that earns her income. In a more literal way than the average person. But anyway and they're like yeah sounds like whatever there's like an actual medical diagnosis for it, but they're like yeah it sounds like that stupid extreme morning sickness be really careful and maybe we're just going to put you on maternity leave early this time. We'll tell the press it's just a vacation. So that then they can write the tabloids about how you had fun on that vacation wink."},
		{"id":"6f1393ae6ad57b2b","type":"text","text":"The wave of nausea hit her harder and faster than usual, so much so that she almost projectile vomited right there on the floor. But Sara managed to swallowed back the acid and breath. She focused on relaxing her body, because she didn't want to lose her dinner, at least not all of it. The longer she kept it down, the more she gave her body a chance to digest it. \n\nThe weirdest part was that familiar stomach pain was finally gone, instead the feeling in her stomach was more that it was... heavy? The sensation was different, but that didn't change the task at hand, if anything this only justified it more. ","x":-12,"y":-3040,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"4ecd540ed7bf5c01","x":1470,"y":3360,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Her stomach collateral damage \n\nIt was like a tug of war, but no one won, the rope snapped. "}
